    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://newyork.craigslist.org/mnh/ret/6046642551.html"></div>
        </div>
Looking for a one talented individual to add to our staff. The job includes floor sales (so experience in wines and spirits is necessary), but will likely also involve cash handling, processing and expediting heavy delivery orders, and -- of course -- providing AMAZING customer service, both in-store and on the phone. This is a demanding job that requires the utmost in efficiency and planning, and also an advanced ability to multi-task.<br>
<br>
Availability will also be key -- the more available you are, the more shifts you open yourself up to. We're open 9am-12am Monday thru Saturday, and 12pm-9pm on Sunday. You MUST be available nights and weekends when needed.<br>
<br>
Finally -- we are a small but rapidly expanding company, and we want great people who want to help us with that growth. And -- while this position is "entry level" -- we need people who can see potential, both in themselves and their role within our store. <br>
<br>
If this sounds like something you'd be interested in, please email me ASAP with your name, contact info, resume, and a brief introduction telling me why and how you're a great fit for our company, and we'll take it from there!!<br>
<br>
Oh -- and a few basic requirements:<br>
<br>
1. Must be able to legally work in the US<br>
2. Must be reliable (absolutely no absences/tardies during first 60 days)<br>
3. Wine and liquor knowledge is a HUGE plus.<br>
4. Must be over 18, preferably over 21.<br>
5. Working geographical knowledge of downtown Manhattan (below Houston) also preferred.<br>
6. Prior wine/liquor store experience highly desired.    </section>

